==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*Of uncertain affinity;

===Pronunciation===
*胃蔚蠈蟼 / theos / theh'-os

===Noun===
{{grc-noun|胃蔚蠈蟼|胃蔚慰峥胃蔚慰峥m|second|theos}}

# a deity, especially (with G3588) the supreme Divinity; figuratively a magistrate; by Hebraism very: - X exceeding, [[God]], god [-ly, -ward].

===Inflection===
{{Template:grc-decl-2nd|胃蔚}}
It is to be noted that Classical Greek contained no vocative singular, while later Greek allowed for both 胃蔚蠈蟼 and 胃蔚苇.

